\par
\b\fs28 17. Update Mechanism\b0\fs20\par
SakayoriMusic ships with an in-app update checker that periodically queries the GitHub Releases API to detect newer versions. When a newer version is detected, the user is informed through a non-modal banner and offered the choice to download and apply the update immediately, to defer the update, or to ignore the specific version. Updates are never applied without user action. On desktop platforms the update is delivered as a new installer that the user launches manually. On the Android platform the update is delivered as an APK that the user installs through the platform's standard package installer flow.\par
The user may disable the update checker through Settings at any time, at the cost of losing automatic awareness of new releases. Disabling the update checker does not disable any other functionality of the software.\par
\par
\b\fs28 18. Localization\b0\fs20\par
SakayoriMusic ships with support for multiple interface languages, selected automatically from the operating system locale and overridable through Settings. The canonical language of the user interface, documentation, release notes, and this agreement is English. Translations are contributed by community volunteers on a best effort basis and may lag behind the English source in completeness or in reflecting the latest terminology. In the event of a conflict between the English text and any translation, the English text controls.\par
\par
\b\fs28 19. Accessibility Commitments\b0\fs20\par
Sakayori Studio strives to make SakayoriMusic usable by people with a wide range of abilities. Ongoing accessibility work includes screen reader compatibility, keyboard navigation, scalable text, high contrast themes, reduced motion settings, and captioning where applicable. Accessibility issues are treated as first class bugs and are prioritized accordingly. Users who encounter accessibility barriers are encouraged to report them through the issue tracker with the accessibility label.\par
