\b\fs28 21. Contributions\b0\fs20\par
Contributions to SakayoriMusic are welcome and are handled on GitHub through pull requests against the main branch of github.com/Sakayorii/sakayori-music. By submitting a contribution, the contributor agrees to release the contribution under the MIT License on the same terms as the rest of the project. Contributors retain copyright over their own contributions and are credited in the project's commit history, release notes, and on request in the Credits screen inside the software under Special Thanks.\par
The project recognizes four tiers of involvement:\par
\i Lead Maintainer\i0 Sakayorii. Final authority on architectural decisions, releases, and brand.\par
\i Co-Maintainers\i0 Currently Lammk. Team members with push access to protected branches but without final authority over release tags. Equal weight in code review discussions.\par
\i Contributors\i0 External individuals who have opened one or more accepted pull requests. Recognized in the Credits screen.\par
\i Special Thanks\i0 Translators, designers, documentation writers, testers, bug reporters with significant contributions, and anyone whose help shaped the project without directly committing code. Recognized in the Credits screen.\par
\par
\b\fs28 22. Code Of Conduct\b0\fs20\par
Participation in the SakayoriMusic community, whether through the GitHub issue tracker, the discussion forum, the Discord server, or any other official channel, is subject to a basic code of conduct grounded in mutual respect, good faith, and inclusive communication. Personal attacks, harassment, targeted hostility toward protected groups, and bad faith argumentation are not tolerated. Moderators may remove offending content and may restrict access to community spaces in response to repeated violations. Appeals may be directed to the Lead Maintainer.\par
\par
\b\fs28 23. Governance And Amendments\b0\fs20\par
This document may be amended to reflect new features, new data flows, new third party services, new contributor tiers, or corrections of errors. Every amendment is accompanied by a version bump of this document and is called out explicitly in the release notes of the version in which the amendment takes effect. The user's acceptance of the amended terms is signaled by continued use of the upgraded software. If the user does not accept an amendment, the user's remedy is to remain on the previous version or to uninstall the software.\par
The commitments enumerated in Section 3 cannot be amended to the detriment of the user without the unanimous agreement of the full maintainer team and without a minimum notice period of ninety days, announced in the release notes of three consecutive versions prior to the amendment taking effect, and accompanied by clear instructions on how the user may uninstall the software before the amendment takes effect.\par
